  "prompt": "I am an Indian married female with a B. Tech in ECE. I worked as a Java developer for 5 years, and am planning to do a MBA in Germany to switch to a non technical role. What are some various job roles, MBA streams and universities to look for?",
  "response": "Here's a comprehensive guide for your MBA and career transition plan:\n\nMBA Streams:\n1. International Business Management\n2. Strategy and Consulting\n3. Marketing Management\n4. Finance and Investment\n5. General Management\n6. Technology Management (given your tech background)\n\nTop German Universities for MBA:\n1. Frankfurt Business School\n2. ESMT Berlin\n3. WHU - Otto Beisheim School of Management\n4. HHL Leipzig Graduate School of Management\n5. TUM School of Management\n6. Berlin School of Economics and Law\n\nPotential Job Roles Post-MBA:\n1. Business Consultant\n2. Product Manager\n3. Strategy Analyst\n4. Marketing Manager\n5. International Business Development\n6. Project Manager\n7. Business Development Executive\n8. Technical Sales/Pre-sales\n\nAdditional Considerations:\n- Look for programs with English instruction\n- Check GMAT/GRE requirements\n- Verify work permit and post-study work visa regulations\n- Consider universities with strong industry connections\n- Explore internship opportunities during MBA\n\nRecommended Steps:\n1. Research university rankings\n2. Prepare for language proficiency tests\n3. Build a strong application portfolio\n4. Network with alumni\n5. Explore scholarship opportunities\n\nWould you like more specific details on any of these aspects?",
